The optimal solution would involve implementing the merge sort algorithm in-place, meaning that the original linked list should be modified to store the sorted result.

The solution should recursively split the linked list into two halves, apply the merge sort algorithm to each half, and then merge the two halves in-place.

When merging two halves, we need to handle the case where the two halves have different lengths.

The solution should be implemented in C++ and Python.

For example, the C++ solution would look like this:

